
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `iceauth` baraye modiriat etela'at dastresi be server-haye ICE (Inter-Client Exchange) estefade mishavad.  Ba estefade az `iceauth`, shoma mitavanid record-haye jadid ezafe konid, record-haye mojood ra taghir dahid, ya record-ha ra hazf konid.  In dastoor bishtar baraye karbarani ke ba barname-haye grafikie kar mikonan mofid ast.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `-f <file>` --> 📁 File-e etela'at dastresi ICE ra moshakhas mikonad. Agar moshakhas nashavad, az `$ICEAUTHORITY` estefade mishavad.
    🔹 `-n` --> ➕ Record-e jadid ezafe mikonad.
    🔹 `-b` --> 🗑️ Record-e mojood ra hazf mikonad.
    🔹 `-l` --> 📜 List-e record-haye dastresi ICE ra namayesh midahad.
    🔹 `-q` --> 🤫 Sedaye kharoji ra kam mikonad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ iceauth -l

    🔹 List kardan hameye record-haye dastresi ICE.

    $ iceauth -n local/hostname:0

    🔹 Ezafe kardan yek record-e jadid baraye dastresi az hostname mahallie ba display number 0.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ iceauth -b local/hostname:0

    🔹 Hazf kardan record-e dastresi baraye hostname mahallie ba display number 0. In karmitune moshkelati ro ke barname ha dar dastresi be server ICE darand hal kone.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `iceauth` command is used to manage ICE (Inter-Client Exchange) authorization information. Using `iceauth`, you can add new entries, modify existing entries, or remove entries.  This command is primarily useful for users working with graphical applications.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `-f <file>` --> 📁 Specifies the ICE authorization file. If not specified, `$ICEAUTHORITY` is used.
    🔹 `-n` --> ➕ Adds a new entry.
    🔹 `-b` --> 🗑️ Removes an existing entry.
    🔹 `-l` --> 📜 Lists the ICE authorization entries.
    🔹 `-q` --> 🤫 Suppresses verbose output.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ iceauth -l

    🔹 List all ICE authorization entries.

    $ iceauth -n local/hostname:0

    🔹 Add a new entry for access from the local hostname with display number 0.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ iceauth -b local/hostname:0

    🔹 Remove the authorization entry for the local hostname with display number 0. This can resolve issues where applications are unable to access the ICE server.
